<subSubSection id="B0E3C1BDFFF11E52FF5DFD94EAD048FD" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F8469236FFF11E52FF5DFD94EAD048FD" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="CA8D4E24FFF11E52FF5DFD94EB484845" bold="true" box="[199,338,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name honors Ana de Lourdes Almendáriz, in recognition of her significant contributions to the 
<collectingCountry id="80EED2A6FFF11E52FE86FDF0EB634819" box="[284,377,583,609]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
herpetofauna knowledge, and her enthusiasm and friendship for many years. Noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
